<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="473" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1566,2023]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1566,1591]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[303,426,1566,1591]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">Coloration</emphasis>
. Chestnut brown. Head and pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[871,971,1566,1591]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1848,1870]" captionTargetBox="[181,1421,1094,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1073,1827]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Pedionis (Pedionis) papillata sp. nov. Male holotype. 5. Habitus, dorsal view; 6. Habitus, lateral view; 7. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 8. Face, facial view. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228903/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
) similar to those in 
<taxonomicName box="[1195,1396,1566,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1195,1396,1566,1591]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">Pedionis aculeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="4" pageNumber="473" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but darker; Scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[471,539,1602,1627]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1848,1870]" captionTargetBox="[181,1421,1094,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1073,1827]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Pedionis (Pedionis) papillata sp. nov. Male holotype. 5. Habitus, dorsal view; 6. Habitus, lateral view; 7. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 8. Face, facial view. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228903/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">
Fig. 
<number box="[524,539,1603,1627]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) dark brown with dark basal triangles; anteclypeus dark brown. Forewing (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1848,1870]" captionTargetBox="[181,1421,1094,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1073,1827]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Pedionis (Pedionis) papillata sp. nov. Male holotype. 5. Habitus, dorsal view; 6. Habitus, lateral view; 7. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 8. Face, facial view. Scale bars: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228903/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
) chestnut brown without hyaline fenestra, subapical cells without dark spots, venation without white spots. Legs dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1566,2023]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">
<emphasis box="[199,363,1710,1735]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[511,592,1710,1735]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1739,1761]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,621,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,611,1718]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Pedionis (Pedionis) papillata sp. nov. Male holotype. 17. Genital capsule, lateral view; 18. Ventral margin of pygophore, ventral view; 19. Style, lateral view; 20. Aedeagus, lateral view; 21. Aedeagus, ventral view; 22. Apex of aedeagus, caudal view; 23. Connective, lateral view; 24. Connective, ventral view; 25. Dorsal connective, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228905/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">
Fig. 
<number box="[563,592,1711,1735]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
) triangular, caudal margin (
<figureCitation box="[901,981,1710,1735]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1739,1761]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,621,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,611,1718]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Pedionis (Pedionis) papillata sp. nov. Male holotype. 17. Genital capsule, lateral view; 18. Ventral margin of pygophore, ventral view; 19. Style, lateral view; 20. Aedeagus, lateral view; 21. Aedeagus, ventral view; 22. Apex of aedeagus, caudal view; 23. Connective, lateral view; 24. Connective, ventral view; 25. Dorsal connective, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228905/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">
Fig. 
<number box="[952,981,1711,1735]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) produced into papilliform process, with four blunt spines; row of short sparse setae along 
<number box="[718,732,1747,1771]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[742,754,1747,1771]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" value="3.0">3</number>
ventral surface. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[1144,1226,1746,1771]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1739,1761]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,621,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,611,1718]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Pedionis (Pedionis) papillata sp. nov. Male holotype. 17. Genital capsule, lateral view; 18. Ventral margin of pygophore, ventral view; 19. Style, lateral view; 20. Aedeagus, lateral view; 21. Aedeagus, ventral view; 22. Apex of aedeagus, caudal view; 23. Connective, lateral view; 24. Connective, ventral view; 25. Dorsal connective, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228905/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">
Fig. 
<number box="[1197,1226,1747,1771]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
) narrow and long, about 
<number box="[220,255,1783,1807]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" value="0.2">0.2</number>
times as long as ventral margin of pygophore; in lateral view, slightly curved dorsally, of uniform width; apex round with long marginal setae. Aedeagal shaft, in lateral view, strongly curved dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1316,1818,1843]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1739,1761]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,621,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,611,1718]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Pedionis (Pedionis) papillata sp. nov. Male holotype. 17. Genital capsule, lateral view; 18. Ventral margin of pygophore, ventral view; 19. Style, lateral view; 20. Aedeagus, lateral view; 21. Aedeagus, ventral view; 22. Apex of aedeagus, caudal view; 23. Connective, lateral view; 24. Connective, ventral view; 25. Dorsal connective, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228905/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">
Fig. 
<number box="[1284,1316,1819,1843]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view, gradually narrowed towards apex (
<figureCitation box="[613,698,1854,1879]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1739,1761]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,621,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,611,1718]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Pedionis (Pedionis) papillata sp. nov. Male holotype. 17. Genital capsule, lateral view; 18. Ventral margin of pygophore, ventral view; 19. Style, lateral view; 20. Aedeagus, lateral view; 21. Aedeagus, ventral view; 22. Apex of aedeagus, caudal view; 23. Connective, lateral view; 24. Connective, ventral view; 25. Dorsal connective, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228905/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">
Fig. 
<number box="[667,698,1855,1879]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
); apex with lateral flanges of denticle margin (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1317,1854,1879]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1739,1761]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,621,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,611,1718]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Pedionis (Pedionis) papillata sp. nov. Male holotype. 17. Genital capsule, lateral view; 18. Ventral margin of pygophore, ventral view; 19. Style, lateral view; 20. Aedeagus, lateral view; 21. Aedeagus, ventral view; 22. Apex of aedeagus, caudal view; 23. Connective, lateral view; 24. Connective, ventral view; 25. Dorsal connective, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228905/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">
Fig. 
<number box="[1285,1317,1855,1879]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
); aedeagal apodeme pooly developed, apex bearing one acute tooth; dorsal connective (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1119,1890,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1739,1761]" captionTargetBox="[167,1424,621,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,611,1718]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25. Pedionis (Pedionis) papillata sp. nov. Male holotype. 17. Genital capsule, lateral view; 18. Ventral margin of pygophore, ventral view; 19. Style, lateral view; 20. Aedeagus, lateral view; 21. Aedeagus, ventral view; 22. Apex of aedeagus, caudal view; 23. Connective, lateral view; 24. Connective, ventral view; 25. Dorsal connective, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228905/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="473">
Fig. 
<number box="[1090,1119,1890,1915]" pageId="4" pageNumber="473" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) in lateral view, M-shaped, distal part dorsally curved without marginal serration.
</paragraph>
